# JavaScript Standards

Vanilla JS only — no bundler, no frameworks. Files live in `src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/javascript/`.

## Structure

- Group related behavior in **namespace objects**: `const Project = { ... }`, `const UI = { ... }`.
- Namespace names: `PascalCase`. Methods and variables: `camelCase`.
- Use `function` for object methods; `const` / `let` for locals (prefer `const` when not reassigned).
- Initialize on `DOMContentLoaded` in page-specific entry files (`index.js`).

## DOM & Events

- Wire interactivity with `addEventListener`; avoid inline `onclick` in HTML.
- Give interactive elements stable `id` attributes; select with `document.querySelector` / `querySelectorAll`.
- Identify timeline/media elements with `item-hash="{hash}"` for lookup via `UI.getElementByHash`.
- Use delegated handlers from `dynamicElementsEvents` for dynamically created elements.

## Drag and Drop

- Namespace custom `dataTransfer` keys with the `video-editor/` prefix:
  `video-editor/media-hash`, `video-editor/clip-hash`, `video-editor/drag-type`, etc.
- Use `DragNDrop` helpers — do not duplicate drag-type detection logic.

## Data & API

- Server-rendered state is injected in the Qute template (`currentProject`); scripts read it, they do not redefine it.
- Use `fetch` for REST calls; handle non-OK responses and surface errors in the UI.
- Prefer `===` / `!==` for comparisons; use `async`/`await` for sequential async work.

## Logging & Errors

```javascript
// ❌ BAD — alert, bare catch, debug noise in production paths
alert('failed');
catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD — structured console levels, early return on missing data
if (!media) {
    console.error('Media not found', hash);
    return;
}
console.debug('Selected element', selectedElement);
```

- `console.error` for failures; `console.debug` for diagnostics.
- Do not leave stray `console.log` calls — remove or downgrade to `debug` before finishing.

## Style

- 4-space indentation; semicolons; single quotes for strings unless escaping is awkward.
- No wildcard or global pollution beyond the declared namespace objects and `currentProject`.
